        -----
        The probability density function for the triangular distribution is

        .. math:: P(x;l, m, r) = \\begin{cases}
                  \\frac{2(x-l)}{(r-l)(m-l)}& \\text{for $l \\leq x \\leq m$},\\\\
                  \\frac{2(r-x)}{(r-l)(r-m)}& \\text{for $m \\leq x \\leq r$},\\\\
